text.tspan: happyland concept
Originally, I created an h and an l with
some segments missing from each
letter. This would represent happyland440's
initials, HL.
I thickened and rounded out the lines, and
conjoined the separate letters to make a
stairlike pattern.
Worried that the letter weren't distinguish-
-able enough, I thickened the lines again and
added a section under the upper-left vertical
segment in order to make it look like an h.
Colour selection

The shape looked strange to me so I added
a straight bottom edge to the piece of the
logo in the middle. I then re-selected the
gradient and made the outline variant.
